Use the standard library
This is how to cycpattern_check of a and b:
   Remember that n is a's length
   Remember that m is b's length
   When m is 0, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   When n is 0, then:
      The answer is 0
   End when
   Remember that aa is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Add aa to item i in a
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Add aa to item i in a
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that pos is find of aa and b
   When pos is less than n, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   The answer is 0
Now you know
>>> cycpattern_check of [97, 98, 99, 100] and [97, 98, 100] 
0
>>> cycpattern_check of [104, 101, 108, 108, 111] and [101, 108, 108] 
1
>>> cycpattern_check of [119, 104, 97, 115, 115, 117, 112] and [112, 115, 117, 115] 
0